/F2 14 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 730 Tm
(1. Motivation) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 711 Tm
(The starting point for this exercise was a Bank class that concentrated most of) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 696 Tm
(the system behaviour in one place. Bank registered branches and accounts, stored) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 681 Tm
(customer contact information, stored branch opening times, moved staff between) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 666 Tm
(branches, changed account balances, applied interest, closed accounts, and) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 651 Tm
(navigated through Payroll to mutate a PaySchedule.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 631 Tm
(This design made Bank a god class. It was not only coordinating banking) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 616 Tm
(operations; it also knew the internal details of accounts, branches, customers,) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 601 Tm
(and payroll. As a result, changes to simple domain rules would tend to affect Bank) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 586 Tm
(even when the relevant data belonged somewhere else.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 566 Tm
(The refactoring therefore focused on redistributing responsibilities while keeping) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 551 Tm
(the observable client behaviour intact. The main reengineering patterns applied) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 536 Tm
(were: move behaviour close to data, remove navigation code, and split up the god) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 521 Tm
(class into smaller collaborating objects.) Tj
/F2 14 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 501 Tm
(2. Account Responsibilities) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 482 Tm
(Account now owns account lifecycle and balance behaviour. The new open_for method) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 467 Tm
(associates an account with a customer. The add_funds method updates the balance) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 452 Tm
(directly on the account. The add_interest method uses the account's own balance) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 437 Tm
(and interest rate to calculate the new balance. The close method clears the) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 422 Tm
(customer reference and resets the balance to zero.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 402 Tm
(This change is motivated by information ownership. The balance and interest rate) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 387 Tm
(are account data, so the operation that changes them should also live on Account.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 372 Tm
(Bank still keeps the list of active accounts, but it no longer performs the) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 357 Tm
(detailed balance calculation itself.) Tj
/F2 14 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 337 Tm
(3. Branch Responsibilities) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 318 Tm
(Branch now owns branch opening times and staff movement. A branch starts with a) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 303 Tm
(default opening time of 9:00, exposes get_opening_time, and provides) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 288 Tm
(change_opening_time. It also provides add_staff_member, transfer_staff_member, and) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 273 Tm
(transfer_all_staff_to.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 253 Tm
(Previously, Bank stored branch opening times in a separate dictionary and) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 238 Tm
(transferred staff by directly modifying the staff lists returned by Branch. That) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 223 Tm
(was navigation code because Bank had to reach into the branch's data structure and) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 208 Tm
(manipulate it. The new design asks Branch to perform those operations itself.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 188 Tm
(When a branch is closed, Bank now delegates staff transfer to the closing branch) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 173 Tm
(and then removes the branch from the bank registry. This keeps Bank as the) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 158 Tm
(coordinator of the closure while Branch handles its own staff collection.) Tj
/F2 14 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 138 Tm
(4. Customer Responsibilities) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 119 Tm
(Customer now owns its contact details. The default address and phone number are) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 104 Tm
(initialised inside Customer as NO ADDRESS and NO PHONE NUMBER. Customer provides) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 89 Tm
(getters and setters for both fields.) Tj
/F1 9 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 40 Tm
(Page 2 of 4) Tj
