/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 710 Tm
(by customer object. That meant customer data was split between Customer and Bank.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 695 Tm
(Moving those fields into Customer makes the model easier to understand: a) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 680 Tm
(customer's name, address, and phone number are all available from the customer) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 665 Tm
(object itself.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 645 Tm
(The client assertions were updated accordingly. They still check that a new) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 630 Tm
(customer receives the expected default address and phone number, but the) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 615 Tm
(assertions now ask the Customer object instead of asking Bank to look up) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 600 Tm
(dictionary values.) Tj
