1 0 0 1 72 580 Tm
(5. Payroll Responsibilities) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 561 Tm
(Payroll now provides change_payroll_date. Bank no longer reaches through Payroll) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 546 Tm
(to obtain a PaySchedule and then call set_pay_date on it. Instead, Bank delegates) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 531 Tm
(the request to Payroll.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 511 Tm
(This removes navigation code and improves encapsulation. PaySchedule remains) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 496 Tm
(unchanged, as requested in the README. Payroll remains responsible for knowing how) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 481 Tm
(staff categories map to pay schedules, while Bank only records the payroll object) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 466 Tm
(involved in the operation and forwards the business request.) Tj
/F2 14 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 446 Tm
(6. Bank After Refactoring) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 427 Tm
(After the changes, Bank still has a useful role. It coordinates the system-level) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 412 Tm
(workflow and maintains the main registries: active accounts, known customers,) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 397 Tm
(branches, and the current payroll reference. What changed is that Bank no longer) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 382 Tm
(owns behaviour that belongs naturally to another object.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 362 Tm
(For example, setup_new_account still belongs in Bank because it registers an) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 347 Tm
(account and ensures the customer is known to the bank. However, the actual) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 332 Tm
(customer association is delegated to Account. Similarly, close_branch still) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 317 Tm
(belongs in Bank because it changes the branch registry, but the staff transfer is) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 302 Tm
(delegated to Branch.) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 282 Tm
(This keeps the design small and conservative. No new external libraries were) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 267 Tm
(introduced, Staff and PaySchedule were left unchanged, and the existing class) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
1 0 0 1 72 252 Tm
(names and client workflow were preserved.) Tj
